  4.8) If Eggdrop dumped a core file when it crashed, it would be very
       useful if you could paste gdb's output during the following steps:

       First, call gdb:
         $ gdb eggdrop -c core

       (Systemd users could try: coredumpctl)

       Then, enter 'bt' on gdb's command line:
         (gdb) bt

       (Even more information with 'bt full')

       Keep your core file for at least one week so the development
       team can ask for further information if needed. Do not send the
       core file unless asked.

       NOTE: If this is a reproducible bug, please compile with:
         meson setup builddir -Dbuildtype=debug
         ninja -C builddir

       This provides better debugging information. It's worth the extra
       compile time to help fix the bug.

